arliament.uk/resources/694282/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694282/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","New Enterprise Allowance: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of New Enterprise Allowance (a) recipients and (b) mentors were women in each NUTS 1 designated region in each year since 2011-12.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","65493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694283","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-01","<p>The number of households affected by the benefit cap by each Local Authority area in Scotland is published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html</a></p><p> </p><p>The latest available data shows the number of households capped at November 2016. The changes in cap levels were rolled-out across Local Authorities from 7 November 2016 to 20 January 2017. Due to this phased implementation of the new levels, and the way in which monthly data on capped households is returned to DWP over a four week rolling period, the main impact of these changes will not be seen in the Benefit Cap Official Statistics until May 2017, when data to February 2017 will first be published.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-03-01T17:53:40.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694283/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694283/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Housing Benefit: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have been affected by the revised benefit cap in each local authority area in Scotland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","65450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694284","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-01","<p>Out of those expected to be affected by the lower benefit cap, the average additional cost per household in the Glasgow Local Authority Area, renting in the private rented sector, is estimated to be an average of £47 per week.</p><p> </p><p>Out of those expected to be affected by the lower benefit cap, the average additional cost per household in the Glasgow Local Authority Area, renting in the social rented sector has been estimated to be an average of £54 per week.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","65452","2017-03-01T17:27:31.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694284/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694284/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Housing Benefit: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the estimated additional cost is to each household in the Glasgow Local Authority Area renting in the private rented sector affected by the revised benefit cap; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","65451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694285","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-01","<p>Out of those expected to be affected by the lower benefit cap, the average additional cost per household in the Glasgow Local Authority Area, renting in the private rented sector, is estimated to be an average of £47 per week.</p><p> </p><p>Out of those expected to be affected by the lower benefit cap, the average additional cost per household in the Glasgow Local Authority Area, renting in the social rented sector has been estimated to be an average of £54 per week.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","65451","2017-03-01T17:27:32.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694285/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694285/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Housing Benefit: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the estimated additional cost is to each household in the Glasgow Local Authority Area renting in social housing affected by the revised benefit cap; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","65452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694286","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-02","<p>There are currently 83 Contract Managers overseeing current live contracts.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-03-02T15:03:57.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694286/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694286/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Department for Work and Pensions: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many officials of his Department oversee contracts awarded to external providers after those contracts have been awarded.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694287","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-01","<p>The amount of time Employment and Support Allowance work-related activity group claimants (and their equivalent in Universal Credit) are supported by their work coach will be tailored to their individual circumstances and support needs. This may include being invited to work focused interviews with their work coach and also offered appropriate support through external provision.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-03-01T15:36:46.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694287/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694287/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the personal support package in the Government's Improving Lives Green Paper, what the minimum number of minutes of support per year will be which people in the employment and support allowance work-related activity group will receive from their work coach.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","65533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694288","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-01","<p>Tell Us Once (TUO) is a voluntary service administered by the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP). It is offered at the time of a verified birth and death by local authorities (LAs). It offers the citizen the option of sharing information with a range of public sector services at one time, avoiding the need for the citizen to separately inform multiple organisations.</p><p> </p><p>The table below gives details on the numbers providing the Birth Service for each of the last 5 years.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of LAs offering TUO birth service</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>222</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>234</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>216</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>201</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>140</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-03-01T17:53:24.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694288/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694288/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Registration of Births, Deaths, Marriages and Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many local authorities offered the Tell Us Once service for registering child births in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","65543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694289","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-01","<p>Tell Us Once is a voluntary service administered by the Department for Work and Pensions. It is offered at the time of a verified birth and death by local authorities (LAs). It offers the citizen the option of sharing information with a range of public sector services at one time, avoiding the need for the citizen to separately inform multiple organisations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Since April 2012 the service has been subject to routine management scrutiny and its performance is regularly reviewed against a range of measures. These include the level of take up by LAs and the blend of channels used by the citizen to access the service. These reveal that take-up and population coverage of the service continue to rise.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-03-01T17:19:22.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694289/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/694289/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-24","Registration of Births, Deaths, Marriages and Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the performance of the Tell Us Once service.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","65544"
