"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693795","Home Office","false","2017-03-02","<p>The need for a DNA test to clarify an applicant’s claim to British nationality is rare, affecting a small number of cases. It is not compulsory to undergo a test to support an application for a passport.</p><p>In light of this, the supervised submission of a sample for DNA testing is conducted in our London office at present. The feasibility of offering this in other passport offices is currently under review. The DNA test itself is conducted in an accredited laboratory.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-03-02T17:20:07.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693795/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693795/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-23","HM Passport Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to enable DNA testing to be carried out in regional passport offices.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","65319"
