"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693832","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-03","<p>Since 2010, psychoactive substances have not been linked to the deaths of any residents of Approved Premises.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-03-03T14:47:25.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693832/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693832/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-23","Bail Hostels: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many deaths where the presence of a novel psychoactive substance was noted occurred in bail hostels, by premises, in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","65251"
