"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693834","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-02","<p>MoJ does not collect data on the number of children who are witnesses in criminal and family courts. However, the Government continues to work with the judiciary and others to improve support and protections for vulnerable witnesses, including children.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-03-02T12:07:42.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693834/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693834/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-23","Witnesses: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many children were witnesses in court in each month of the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","65253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693835","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-05","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office and is included in the reply</p><p><br>Information on the total number of civil servants overseeing contracts awarded to external providers is not centrally held.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","65056","2017-04-05T08:14:01.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693835/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693835/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-02-23","Prime Minister: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants in 10 Downing Street oversee contracts which have been awarded to external providers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693836","Prime Minister","false","2017-03-03","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the press release following my address to the Republican Party, a transcript of which can be found on gov.uk website.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-03-03T13:58:21.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693836/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693836/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-02-23","Prime Minister: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, in what capacity her address to the Republican Party in Philadelphia on 26 January 2017 was given.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","65321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693837","Public Accounts Commission","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Public Accounts Commission does not have any employees (including civil servants) and is not responsible for any contracts. It is a statutory body with a membership of nine Members of the House of Commons. Its role is defined by the National Audit Act 1983 and the Budget Responsibility and National Audit Act 2011. Its principal duties under the Acts are to examine the National Audit Office Estimate and lay it before the House, to consider reports from the appointed auditor of the National Audit Office (NAO), to appoint non-executive members of the NAO Board, and to report from time to time.</p>","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh",,"2017-02-27T14:22:30.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693837/answer","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693837/answer",,,,,"24","Public Accounts Commission","Public Accounts Commission","2017-02-23","Public Accounts Commission: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chairman of the Public Accounts Commission, how many civil servants in the Commission oversee contracts which have been awarded to external providers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693838","Scotland Office","false","2017-03-03","<p>Other than minor or bespoke purchases, the Scotland Office does not normally undertake direct procurement or tendering projects. It utilises existing service contracts between suppliers and the Scottish Government or the Ministry of Justice. The Scotland Office have no civil servants whose sole role is to oversee contracts which have been awarded to external providers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-03-03T12:30:04.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693838/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693838/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-23","Scotland Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many civil servants in his Department oversee contracts which have been awarded to external providers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693839","Scotland Office","false","2017-03-01","<p>I have regular discussions with my Cabinet colleagues and we are carefully considering sectoral priorities ahead of negotiations to leave the EU.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-03-01T14:01:53.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693839/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693839/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-23","Brexit: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on the priorities for the (a) steel and (b) fishing industry within the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","65242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693840","Scotland Office","false","2017-03-01","<p>DWP are working to recruit more work coaches to support people into work in Scotland and we do not expect there to be a change in service as a result of the proposed closures. The UK Government is committed to retaining a Jobcentre network and continuing to serve people in all areas of the country to make sure they can continue to access the services they need, responding to economic trends and the changing ways in which claimants access services.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-03-01T14:03:48.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693840/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693840/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-23","Unemployment: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the effect of recent and proposed closures in the Department for Work and Pensions estate in Scotland on the level of unemployment in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","65300"
