"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693843","Department for Transport","false","2017-02-28","<p>The numbers of participants in speed awareness courses, which a driver may be awarded instead of a charge for a speeding offence, are published by the National Driver Offender Retraining Scheme (NDORS). NDORS’ website gives the details for attendance for the last three years (UK figures) as follows:</p><p> </p><p>2014 1,185,860</p><p>2015 1,207,570</p><p>2016 1,188,961</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-02-28T14:44:57.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693843/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693843/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-23","Road Traffic Offences: Speed Limits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many motorists have taken speed awareness courses after being charged with speeding offences in each of the last there years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","65327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693844","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-03","<p>Rebecca Coriam disappeared from a Bahamas registered vessel in non-UK waters. The Marine Accident Investigation Branch (MAIB) therefore has no jurisdiction in this case and did not initiate an investigation.</p><p> </p><p>An investigation was undertaken by authorities in the Bahamas and the Chief Inspector wrote to the Bahamas Maritime Authority to register the UK as a substantially interested state pursuant to the International Maritime Organization’s Casualty Investigation Code.</p><p> </p><p>MAIB has received one request from a third party into the information it holds on the case.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","65280","2017-03-03T11:23:55.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693844/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693844/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-23","Rebecca Coriam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what factors his Department took into account in taking the decision to discontinue the Marine Accident Investigation Branch inquiry into the disappearance of Rebecca Coriam from the Disney Wonder cruise ship.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","65304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693845","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-03","<p>Northern Powerhouse Rail, sometimes called HS3, is the Government’s vision for dramatically faster and more frequent rail journeys across the North, to help build the Northern Powerhouse and strengthen the British economy.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is working closely with Transport for the North to assess the case for Northern Powerhouse Rail (NPR) including whether the NPR network can serve key markets such as Bradford.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","65380 ; 65383","2017-03-03T11:18:11.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693845/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693845/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-23","Railways: Bradford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has held with Transport for the North on including a Bradford station on the Northern Powerhouse Rail.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","65379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693846","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-03","<p>Northern Powerhouse Rail, sometimes called HS3, is the Government’s vision for dramatically faster and more frequent rail journeys across the North, to help build the Northern Powerhouse and strengthen the British economy.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is working closely with Transport for the North to assess the case for Northern Powerhouse Rail (NPR) including whether the NPR network can serve key markets such as Bradford.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","65379 ; 65383","2017-03-03T11:18:11.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693846/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/693846/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-23","Railways: Bradford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has held with Transport for the North about the potential economic benefits to Bradford of the planned Northern Powerhouse Rail.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","65380"
